Overall Flow / Logic Summary
1.	Page loads → Shows brand name, logo, and welcome message.
2.	User sees a big "Get Started" button.
3.	User clicks button → Browser opens Log-in.html page.
4.	From there, user can create account or login, then go to main site.


Toggle Buttons
•	Two buttons side by side: "Login" and "Create Account".
•	When the page loads, "Login" is active (orange background, white text), and "Create Account" is inactive (white background, gray text).
•	Clicking either button switches the active style and shows the correct form below.
Login Form
•	Shown by default.
•	Contains two input fields: Email and Password. Both are required.
•	A login button styled with orange background; becomes darker orange when hovered.
•	A hidden red message area to show errors like empty fields or wrong details.
Register Form
•	Hidden at first; appears when "Create Account" is clicked.
•	Has four fields: Full Name, Email, Password, and Confirm Password — all required.
•	A create account button with same style as login button.
•	Hidden red message area to show errors like empty fields, mismatched passwords, or duplicate emails.
Success Message Box
•	Hidden at first.
•	Green background with check icon.
•	Shows a success message after account creation or successful login.
•	Has a button to go back to login form.
