Part 3 – JavaScript Logic: How Everything Works
This part controls all interactions, form switching, data saving, and validation.
1. Switching Between Forms
•	When "Login" tab is clicked:
o	Login form appears, register form hides.
o	Login tab becomes active style, register tab becomes inactive.
o	Success message box hides if open.
•	When "Create Account" tab is clicked:
o	Register form appears, login form hides.
o	Register tab becomes active style, login tab becomes inactive.
o	Success message box hides if open.
2. Register Function (registerUser())
This runs when user clicks "Create Account".
1.	Get values from all input fields and remove extra spaces.
2.	Check empty fields: if any field is empty, show error message "Please fill in all fields."
3.	Check password match: if password and confirm password are different, show error "Passwords do not match."
4.	Check existing email:
o	Get saved user list from browser storage; if empty, start with empty list.
o	Check if entered email already exists in the list.
o	If exists, show error "An account with this email already exists."
5.	Save new account:
o	If all checks pass, add new user data (name, email, password) to the list.
o	Save updated list back to browser storage.
6.	Show success:
o	Hide register form, show success message "Your account has been created successfully!"
3. Login Function (loginUser())
This runs when user clicks "Login".
1.	Get values from email and password fields, remove extra spaces.
2.	Check empty fields: if empty, show error "Please fill in all fields."
3.	Check credentials:
o	Get saved user list from browser storage.
o	Look for a user where email and password both match what was entered.
4.	Result:
o	If match found: hide login form, show success message "Welcome back, [Name]! You are now logged in."
o	If no match: show error "Invalid email or password."
4. Go to Login Function (goToLogin())
•	Triggered when user clicks "Go to Login" button inside success message.
•	Automatically clicks the Login tab to switch back to login form.
