Part 3 – JavaScript Logic: How Everything Works
This part controls all interactive functions.
1. Cart System
•	let cart = []: creates empty list to store selected items.
addToCart(name, price)
•	Runs when clicking "Add to Cart".
•	Adds item name and price into cart list.
•	Calls updateCart() to refresh display.
removeFromCart(index)
•	Runs when clicking trash icon.
•	Removes specific item from cart list by its position number.
•	Calls updateCart() to refresh display.
updateCart()
•	Updates cart count number in header.
•	If cart is empty → shows "Your cart is empty" message.
•	If has items → hides empty message, shows each item with price, calculates total.
•	Updates total price in both cart section and order summary.
•	Converts prices to 2 decimal places for correct currency format.
•	Note: In current code, currency symbol shows $ but should be ₱ to match prices displayed — this can be updated easily.
2. Order Form Handling
•	Listens for form submit event.
•	Stops page from reloading.
•	Hides form, shows success message.
•	Clears cart list and updates display so next order starts fresh.
3. Feedback Star Rating
•	Selects all star icons and hidden input field.
•	When clicking a star:
o	Stores selected rating number in hidden input.
o	Resets all stars to gray.
o	Turns yellow all stars up to the one clicked.
•	When feedback form submitted:
o	Hides form, shows thank you message.
o	Resets stars back to gray, clears name and comment fields.
________________________________________Overall Program Flow
1.	Page loads → User sees header, welcome message and menu.
2.	User browses menu → Clicks "Add to Cart" → Items appear in cart with total calculated.
3.	User goes to Cart → Clicks "Proceed to Order" → Fills delivery details and selects payment → Submits → Success message shown.
4.	User can go to Feedback page → Gives rating and comments → Submits → Thank you message shown.
5.	User can view Contact page anytime for information.

